abstract: ABC’s “High School Musical: Get in the Picture,” a new reality show based on the highly successful movies on Disney Channel (which is a corporate sibling), made a lackluster debut in the ratings on Sunday, drawing just 4 million viewers at 8 p.m., according to Nielsen’s estimates.
